851
01:17:11,349 --> 01:17:12,908
Don't pee on us.

852
01:17:12,933 --> 01:17:15,856
This sounds spectacular.

853
01:17:17,376 --> 01:17:20,314
Why now?
Why her?

854
01:17:20,366 --> 01:17:22,503
Because she
hasn't given up.

855
01:17:22,528 --> 01:17:24,804
You think she can fix it.

856
01:17:25,226 --> 01:17:27,285
What makes
you say that?

857
01:17:29,713 --> 01:17:31,787
Can she, Athena?

858
01:17:32,024 --> 01:17:34,023
I have no idea.

859
01:17:34,906 --> 01:17:37,190
Let's go find out.

860
01:17:48,313 --> 01:17:50,352
Hold on.

861
01:17:50,377 --> 01:17:53,395
Is this-
Is this normal?

862
01:17:57,194 --> 01:18:00,934
What... is... happen... ing...?

863
01:18:12,980 --> 01:18:15,438
I'm thirsty.
I'm dying.

864
01:18:15,463 --> 01:18:16,694
I think I'm dying.

865
01:18:16,719 --> 01:18:18,876
- I'm dying. I'm dying.
- You're not dying.

866
01:18:18,901 --> 01:18:21,139
There's coke
in the fridge.

867
01:18:39,067 --> 01:18:40,654
Help yourself.

868
01:18:40,820 --> 01:18:43,476
We have no idea
how many are here.

869
01:18:43,501 --> 01:18:45,442
But we're damn sure
they know we're coming. So.

870
01:18:45,467 --> 01:18:49,446
We move quickly, you follow me.
No questions, got it?

871
01:18:50,413 --> 01:18:52,198
- Got it.
- Alright.

872
01:18:59,799 --> 01:19:01,565
Excuse me.

873
01:19:23,300 --> 01:19:24,636
We're in Paris?

874
01:19:24,661 --> 01:19:26,281
Would you stop
being so amazed?

875
01:19:26,306 --> 01:19:29,269
- I thought you wanted me to be amazed.
- I want you to stop yapping.

876
01:19:29,294 --> 01:19:35,308
<i>(French speaker over PA)</i>

877
01:19:35,333 --> 01:19:36,776
Tower's closing.

878
01:19:36,801 --> 01:19:38,916
Oh, hell.

879
01:19:43,696 --> 01:19:45,184
Come here.

880
01:19:45,395 --> 01:19:47,468
Now. You and I are gonna
be on their watch list.

881
01:19:47,493 --> 01:19:50,821
They may not have your facial
recognition profile uploaded yet.

882
01:19:50,846 --> 01:19:52,589
- May not?
- May not, so...

883
01:19:52,614 --> 01:19:55,463
You walk over there, you take
this, you tap him on the neck.

884
01:19:55,464 --> 01:19:57,010
If he's human,
it knocks him right out.

885
01:19:57,035 --> 01:19:58,814
And if it's a robot?

886
01:19:59,866 --> 01:20:02,175
- Hey.
- Then you'll just pissed it off.

887
01:20:02,274 --> 01:20:04,005
Fantastic.

888
01:20:06,907 --> 01:20:09,056
She got guts.
You gotta give her that.

889
01:20:16,066 --> 01:20:17,606
Human!

890
01:20:33,983 --> 01:20:36,337
The French hated this thing
when Eiffel first unveiled it

891
01:20:36,362 --> 01:20:39,300
at the Paris World's Fair.
They thought it was an eyesore.

892
01:20:39,325 --> 01:20:42,300
Eiffel didn't care though. It wasn't
meant to be a monument.

893
01:20:42,325 --> 01:20:44,482
It was meant to find
another world.

894
01:20:44,507 --> 01:20:47,142
Le cat premiere.

895
01:20:47,167 --> 01:20:48,670
Plus Ultra's first four.

896
01:20:48,695 --> 01:20:50,339
They were a
part of all this?

897
01:20:50,364 --> 01:20:55,606
Eiffel, Jules Verne,
Tesla, and Mr. Edison.

898
01:20:56,893 --> 01:20:58,247
They designed this
antenna that we're inside...

899
01:20:58,272 --> 01:21:00,154
Wait, what?
The Eiffel Tower's an antenna?

900
01:21:00,139 --> 01:21:02,526
Now I finally answer your question.
Are you gonna interrupt me?

901
01:21:02,551 --> 01:21:07,028
Yes, Tesla designed the antenna to
observe every kind of frequency out there.

902
01:21:07,053 --> 01:21:09,498
Subspace, trans-dimensional,
you name it.

903
01:21:09,523 --> 01:21:12,146
And, they found exactly what
they were looking for.

904
01:21:12,171 --> 01:21:14,194
And then, Edison tried to
take credit for it,

905
01:21:14,219 --> 01:21:16,975
- because these two hate each other they....
- Frank.

906
01:21:17,000 --> 01:21:18,661
Stay on topic.

907
01:21:18,686 --> 01:21:20,047
Yeah.

908
01:21:21,543 --> 01:21:25,800
There were all these rumors,
of a secret entrance...

909
01:21:25,825 --> 01:21:31,941
the four kept just for themselves,
a one way ticket...

910
01:21:32,172 --> 01:21:34,910
in case of emergencies.

911
01:21:38,293 --> 01:21:40,239
The Spectacle.

912
01:22:12,373 --> 01:22:14,942
You ain't seen nothing yet, kid.

913
01:23:09,810 --> 01:23:13,267
Oh no.
The tour is over.

914
01:23:19,906 --> 01:23:22,034
It's a rocket.

915
01:23:25,813 --> 01:23:27,690
They're coming.

916
01:23:28,352 --> 01:23:29,838
Alright.

917
01:23:47,806 --> 01:23:49,553
Buckle up.

918
01:24:06,417 --> 01:24:09,115
- What'd he say?
- Pretty much what you'd expect.

919
01:24:09,140 --> 01:24:11,238
Tell them to hang on.

920
01:24:24,936 --> 01:24:28,169
WOO...  HOO...!

921
01:25:21,988 --> 01:25:24,148
- Why are we going back?
- We're not.

922
01:25:24,173 --> 01:25:26,769
We're going through.
To another dimension.

923
01:25:26,794 --> 01:25:30,256
So we blasted into outer space
just to get a running start?

924
01:25:30,281 --> 01:25:32,867
This part may
get a little weird.

925
01:26:28,087 --> 01:26:29,578
Casey.

926
01:26:29,613 --> 01:26:31,335
Wake up.

927
01:26:33,059 --> 01:26:34,636
Casey?

928
01:26:35,920 --> 01:26:38,522
Casey.
Wake up.

929
01:26:38,547 --> 01:26:40,389
We're here.

930
01:27:26,466 --> 01:27:27,986
Now what?

931
01:27:29,179 --> 01:27:30,837
You tell me.

932
01:27:31,186 --> 01:27:33,195
I tell you?
This was your idea.

933
01:27:33,220 --> 01:27:36,679
I don't have ideas. I just
find the people who do.

934
01:27:36,704 --> 01:27:38,622
- So there's no plan.
- There's a plan.

935
01:27:38,647 --> 01:27:40,881
You just haven't
come up with it yet.

936
01:27:41,326 --> 01:27:44,287
But, you should
do that soon.

937
01:27:47,587 --> 01:27:49,950
That's just terrific.

938
01:27:50,066 --> 01:27:52,260
Here. Hide this.

939
01:27:52,833 --> 01:27:53,760
Absolutely.

940
01:27:53,785 --> 01:27:57,856
Wait, is that the 1 kiloton detonation
thingy you told me not to play with?

941
01:27:57,881 --> 01:27:59,286
Right now,
it's our insurance policy.

942
01:27:59,311 --> 01:28:01,691
There's a good chance they're gonna
try and kill us right at the gate.

943
01:28:01,716 --> 01:28:03,909
So we're just
gonna stand here?

944
01:28:03,934 --> 01:28:07,769
Well, you wanted to see Tomorrowland.

945
01:28:07,794 --> 01:28:09,700
Here it comes.

946
01:28:35,451 --> 01:28:37,222
Take the bag.

947
01:28:42,786 --> 01:28:45,503
- Frank.
- David.

948
01:28:45,693 --> 01:28:47,511
You look well.

949
01:28:47,536 --> 01:28:49,067
Age becomes you.

950
01:28:49,092 --> 01:28:51,302
Thanks.
You should try it.

951
01:28:51,327 --> 01:28:54,552
I don't know. I think I'll just keep
drinking my shake every morning.

952
01:28:54,577 --> 01:28:56,276
Comes in chocolate now.

953
01:28:56,301 --> 01:28:57,769
Yum.

954
01:29:00,684 --> 01:29:02,324
Hello, Athena.

955
01:29:02,349 --> 01:29:05,103
Started to think you
were never coming home.

956
01:29:05,335 --> 01:29:07,620
Where oh where
have you been?

957
01:29:07,621 --> 01:29:08,900
Doing my job.

958
01:29:08,901 --> 01:29:10,599
Your job?

959
01:29:10,624 --> 01:29:14,335
I'm sorry, were we not clear when we
suspended your recruitment protocols?

960
01:29:14,360 --> 01:29:16,928
I got that since when you
called me bloody obsolete

961
01:29:16,953 --> 01:29:19,357
