everyone it was just an elaborate hoax...

966
01:29:33,080 --> 01:29:37,648
Unfortunately, for all of us, it
doesn't really matter now, does it?

967
01:29:37,673 --> 01:29:39,700
Why doesn't it matter?

968
01:29:41,028 --> 01:29:43,221
And who might you be?

969
01:29:43,246 --> 01:29:47,392
I'm- I'm Casey
Newton.

970
01:29:48,180 --> 01:29:50,871
And who-
who might you be?

971
01:29:50,896 --> 01:29:54,882
David Nix.
Pleasure.

972
01:29:54,973 --> 01:29:57,310
Well, Frank, it's been
wonderful catching up.

973
01:29:57,335 --> 01:30:00,513
But as we were fairly clear
about the terms of your exile,

974
01:30:00,538 --> 01:30:02,703
and the consequences of violating it,

975
01:30:02,728 --> 01:30:04,007
I have to ask.

976
01:30:04,032 --> 01:30:05,909
What the hell
are you doing here?

977
01:30:05,934 --> 01:30:08,231
I think she
can fix it.

978
01:30:11,292 --> 01:30:12,679
I'm sorry, I...

979
01:30:12,704 --> 01:30:15,586
Her. I think she
can fix it, David.

980
01:30:15,611 --> 01:30:16,754
Wait, what?

981
01:30:16,779 --> 01:30:19,206
I've been pirating your signal.
Every time you turn it on here,

982
01:30:19,231 --> 01:30:20,640
I can see it there.

983
01:30:20,665 --> 01:30:25,264
And it flickered.
The percentage dropped, David.

984
01:30:25,780 --> 01:30:27,142
Impossible.

985
01:30:27,167 --> 01:30:29,041
You don't believe me,
let's go find out, right now.

986
01:30:29,079 --> 01:30:31,439
I'm sorry,
what can I fix?

987
01:30:31,464 --> 01:30:37,834
The world, Ms. Newton. He
thinks you can fix the world.

988
01:31:00,159 --> 01:31:03,354
Is that like a
portal to Earth?

989
01:31:03,379 --> 01:31:07,641
No.
It is a bridge way to Earth.

990
01:31:12,238 --> 01:31:15,577
Welcome back to
The Monitor, Frank.

991
01:31:15,859 --> 01:31:18,077
It's something, isn't it?

992
01:31:18,592 --> 01:31:20,831
Yeah, it's something.

993
01:31:36,559 --> 01:31:38,774
Don't worry about
the light show.

994
01:31:38,799 --> 01:31:40,832
It's perfectly safe.

995
01:31:43,413 --> 01:31:46,555
- Am I supposed to do something?
- No.

996
01:31:46,580 --> 01:31:49,715
Okay, can you be a bit more specific
because fixing the world sounds a little...

997
01:31:49,740 --> 01:31:52,028
Just be yourself.

998
01:31:52,499 --> 01:31:54,233
Gotcha.

999
01:31:58,707 --> 01:32:00,082
What are those?

1000
01:32:00,107 --> 01:32:02,232
Flashes of future.

1001
01:32:02,617 --> 01:32:05,084
That's a few seconds from now.

1002
01:32:05,109 --> 01:32:09,107
This whole tower
funnels energy by tachyon.

1003
01:32:09,132 --> 01:32:11,454
A particle that moves
significantly faster than light.

1004
01:32:11,479 --> 01:32:14,201
We discovered them
almost forty years ago.

1005
01:32:14,226 --> 01:32:18,077
Your physicists are still
arguing over whether they exist.

1006
01:32:20,640 --> 01:32:24,147
Oh, dear.
Too late.

1007
01:32:40,078 --> 01:32:42,685
So.
On with the show.

1008
01:32:43,300 --> 01:32:45,418
We've enhanced the
interface significantly.

1009
01:32:45,443 --> 01:32:48,788
There's still functions on
your original algorithm.

1010
01:32:49,813 --> 01:32:52,129
