this machine so that we could

1026
01:34:09,578 --> 01:34:11,607
keep in touch.

1027
01:34:12,120 --> 01:34:14,116
This is 3 days ago.

1028
01:34:14,141 --> 01:34:15,683
Relatively.

1029
01:34:16,893 --> 01:34:20,153
That's
space-time humor.

1030
01:34:22,046 --> 01:34:25,276
Because tachyons
travel faster than light,

1031
01:34:25,301 --> 01:34:26,876
once we harness them...

1032
01:34:26,901 --> 01:34:29,710
You can see
backwards in time.

1033
01:34:29,760 --> 01:34:31,743
Not just backwards.

1034
01:34:33,900 --> 01:34:35,665
You're kidding.

1035
01:34:36,026 --> 01:34:37,386
No.

1036
01:35:01,599 --> 01:35:03,134
What happened?

1037
01:35:03,159 --> 01:35:04,821
Keep going.

1038
01:35:05,233 --> 01:35:07,219
Just a little further.

1039
01:35:53,901 --> 01:35:55,631
That's enough.

1040
01:35:56,660 --> 01:35:58,708
That's enough, kid.

1041
01:36:03,860 --> 01:36:06,180
That's my house.

1042
01:36:06,522 --> 01:36:10,347
Would have been nice, if Frank
had prepared you for this.

1043
01:36:10,372 --> 01:36:13,294
I'm afraid the world is ending.

1044
01:36:13,319 --> 01:36:19,170
It is certain, it is
unavoidable, and it is coming.

1045
01:36:19,373 --> 01:36:20,790
When?

1046
01:36:21,546 --> 01:36:24,083
This is 58 days from now.

1047
01:36:24,108 --> 01:36:26,441
58 days?

1048
01:36:26,466 --> 01:36:29,923
Whatever caused this, could happen
anytime after the static starts.

1049
01:36:29,948 --> 01:36:33,388
It could be a month,
could be sooner.

1050
01:36:42,436 --> 01:36:45,322
Still looking for your flicker, Frank?

1051
01:36:45,347 --> 01:36:47,322
I know what I saw.

1052
01:36:48,495 --> 01:36:50,947
So why aren't you
telling anyone?

1053
01:36:50,972 --> 01:36:55,678
The whole planet is gonna die,
and you're just, sitting here?

1054
01:36:56,180 --> 01:36:58,157
We're not gonna die.

1055
01:36:58,182 --> 01:37:00,478
This is your world, not ours.

1056
01:37:00,503 --> 01:37:02,161
We'll be perfectly
fine here.

1057
01:37:02,172 --> 01:37:05,436
Then why don't
you let people in?

1058
01:37:05,809 --> 01:37:09,249
- Tell her, David.
- Oh, Frank.

1059
01:37:09,792 --> 01:37:13,190
All those years in exile and
you still don't understand.

1060
01:37:13,215 --> 01:37:16,348
These people are...
They're driven by savagery.

1061
01:37:16,373 --> 01:37:19,406
If we told them
about this place,

1062
01:37:19,880 --> 01:37:23,291
then that, would
happen here, to us.

1063
01:37:23,316 --> 01:37:24,881
Then nothing would survive.

1064
01:37:24,906 --> 01:37:27,272
But it hasn't happened yet.

1065
01:37:27,297 --> 01:37:29,842
Actually it has happened.
You just haven't accepted it.

1066
01:37:29,867 --> 01:37:32,245
Well I don't accept it.

1067
01:37:38,558 --> 01:37:40,951
You see that?
Did you see that?

1068
01:37:40,976 --> 01:37:43,996
David, I know that you saw that.
That means that there is a chance.

1069
01:37:44,021 --> 01:37:46,176
There's at
least a chance.

1070
01:37:53,062 --> 01:37:54,962
That went quite well,
don't you think?

1071
01:37:54,987 --> 01:37:56,494
What happened?

1072
01:37:56,519 --> 01:37:58,612
You're being deported...

1073
01:37:59,213 --> 01:38:00,536
again.

1074
01:38:00,561 --> 01:38:03,268
Well,
that's Nix for you.

1075
01:38:03,293 --> 01:38:05,558
No new ideas.

1076
01:38:05,680 --> 01:38:09,022
Apparently your 1/10.000
furball in the inevitability

1077
01:38:09,047 --> 01:38:12,242
wasn’t convincing enough
to change his mind.

1078
01:38:17,446 --> 01:38:19,161
Be gentle.

1079
01:38:29,819 --> 01:38:31,459
You okay?

1080
01:38:32,931 --> 01:38:36,740
I know you think somewhere in the
zillions of questions that I was asking you,

1081
01:38:36,765 --> 01:38:40,593
you could've said, "Oh, Casey.
Well that's stuff not really the issue

1082
01:38:40,618 --> 01:38:44,813
because our future predicting machine
says we're all gonna die."

1083
01:38:44,838 --> 01:38:46,716
He did sort of
hinted at it.

1084
01:38:46,741 --> 01:38:49,951
This place has nothing
to do with hope.

1085
01:38:49,976 --> 01:38:52,754
- It's the opposite of hope.
- Come on, don't say that.

1086
01:38:52,779 --> 01:38:56,388
Why not?
You said it.

1087
01:38:56,683 --> 01:38:58,499
No wonder you gave up.

1088
01:38:58,524 --> 01:39:00,693
That's before I knew about you.

1089
01:39:00,718 --> 01:39:02,819
You really...

1090
01:39:02,844 --> 01:39:03,994
You really are special.

1091
01:39:04,019 --> 01:39:06,521
Why do you people
keep saying that to me?

1092
01:39:08,732 --> 01:39:10,783
I'm not.

1093
01:39:14,844 --> 01:39:17,263
Why'd you even give me this?
Hm.

1094
01:39:17,288 --> 01:39:22,547
You showed me a place, that was
amazing and incredible, and it was a lie.

1095
01:39:23,677 --> 01:39:25,518
If you're gonna zap an
idea into people's heads,

1096
01:39:25,543 --> 01:39:27,291
you should really make
sure that it's the truth.

1097
01:39:27,316 --> 01:39:30,302
Because you can't do that.
You can't just zap...

1098
01:39:40,063 --> 01:39:41,541
What?

1099
01:39:42,157 --> 01:39:44,674
You zap an idea
into people's heads.

1100
01:39:47,671 --> 01:39:50,228
You were pirating the signal.
How?

1101
01:39:50,253 --> 01:39:51,637
- What?
- At your house,

1102
01:39:51,662 --> 01:39:53,460
all your TVs,
your doomsday room.

1103
01:39:53,485 --> 01:39:55,388
You were boosting the feed
from that Monitor thing.

1104
01:39:55,413 --> 01:39:57,176
- How did you do that?
- No big deal.

1105
01:39:57,201 --> 01:40:00,761
They're running so much power through
it now, a ham radio can pick it up.

1106
01:40:00,786 --> 01:40:03,722
It's just a matter of
finding the right frequency.

1107
01:40:04,966 --> 01:40:07,268
You grabbed a signal from
another dimension.

1108
01:40:07,293 --> 01:40:11,082
From a machine here. That
means it's transmitting there.

1109
01:40:11,107 --> 01:40:14,670
What if it's not just
predicting the future.

1110
01:40:14,695 --> 01:40:16,152
He's broadcasting it.

1111
01:40:16,177 --> 01:40:18,751
When I touched this thing,
for a few minutes,

1112
01:40:18,776 --> 01:40:20,434
it felt like anything
was possible.

1113
01:40:20,459 --> 01:40:23,112
So then why can't the
opposite happen?

1114
01:40:23,137 --> 01:40:25,761
What if The Monitor
is just a giant pin,

1115
01:40:25,786 --> 01:40:29,648
but instead of making you think positive,
it makes you think negative. And it...

1116
01:40:31,179 --> 01:40:32,618
And it's...

1117
01:40:33,151 --> 01:40:36,673
convincing the whole world
to feed the wrong wolf.

1118
01:40:37,336 --> 01:40:39,683
We need to turn
that thing off.

1119
01:40:44,711 --> 01:40:46,812
It's time
to go home.

1120
01:40:52,402 --> 01:40:54,664
David.
David.

1121
01:40:54,851 --> 01:40:57,902
- Ah! It's uninhabited and uncharted.
- Listen to me.

1122
01:40:57,927 --> 01:41:00,397
But it looks like a lovely
place to spend your last days.

1123
01:41:00,422 --> 01:41:02,987
David, The Monitor is
acting as an antenna.

1124
01:41:03,012 --> 01:41:05,051
It isn't just receiving tachyons,

1125
01:41:05,076 --> 01:41:07,789
it is taking a possible
future and making it like...

1126
01:41:07,814 --> 01:41:10,134
Amplifying it, transmitting
it, like a feedback loop.

1127
01:41:10,159 --> 01:41:13,420
It's a self-fulfilling prophecy
that is coming from right there.

1128
01:41:13,445 --> 01:41:15,328
But it's not just showing people
the end of the world.

1129
01:41:15,353 --> 01:41:16,895
It's giving them the idea
over and over

1130
01:41:16,920 --> 01:41:19,383
- and over again until they just accept it.
- It's a ticking time bomb.

1131
01:41:19,408 --> 01:41:20,675
And we're the ones
that lit the fuse.

1132
01:41:20,700 --> 01:41:23,512
We still have 58 days
to try and change things,

1133
01:41:23,537 --> 01:41:26,309
 but nothing will work as long
as that thing is still on.

1134
01:41:26,333 --> 01:41:30,332
Young lady, I'm gonna assume that your
knowledge of tachyonic fusion is a little sketchy.

1135
01:41:30,357 --> 01:41:33,768
Shutting it down is impossible.

1136
01:41:33,793 --> 01:41:36,145
There is no 'Off'.

1137
01:41:36,170 --> 01:41:40,483
I'm telling you what it's doing.
Why don't you care?

1138
01:41:41,116 --> 01:41:43,694
Because he's the one
that's doing it.

1139
01:41:49,252 --> 01:41:50,744
Right?

1140
01:41:54,508 --> 01:41:56,141
Let's imagine

1141
01:41:57,414 --> 01:41:59,998
If you glimpse the future,

1142
01:42:00,023 --> 01:42:03,416
and were frightened by what you saw,
what would you do with that information?

1143
01:42:03,441 --> 01:42:06,947
Would you go to
politicians?

1144
01:42:06,972 --> 01:42:09,412
Captains of industry?
And how would you convince them?

1145
01:42:09,437 --> 01:42:12,204
With data, facts?

1146
01:42:12,485 --> 01:42:13,641
Good luck.

1147
01:42:13,666 --> 01:42:15,215
The only facts they won't challenge,

1148
01:42:15,240 --> 01:42:17,323
are the ones that keep
the wheels greased,

1149
01:42:17,348 --> 01:42:19,141
and the dollars rolling in.

1150
01:42:19,166 --> 01:42:23,610
But what if there was a way
of skipping the middle man,

1151
01:42:23,635 --> 01:42:28,074
and putting the critical news
directly into everyone's head.

1152
01:42:28,747 --> 01:42:32,707
The probability of widespread
annihilation kept going up.

1153
01:42:32,732 --> 01:42:36,386
The only way to
stop it, was to show it.

1154
01:42:36,411 --> 01:42:37,719
To scare people straight.

1155
01:42:37,744 --> 01:42:41,481
What reasonable human
being wouldn't be galvanized

1156
01:42:41,505 --> 01:42:45,429
by the potential destruction of
everything we've ever known or loved.

1157
01:42:46,498 --> 01:42:49,116
To save civilization,

1158
01:42:49,307 --> 01:42:52,152
I would show it's collapse.

1159
01:42:52,561 --> 01:42:55,642
But how do you think this
vision was received?

1160
01:42:55,667 --> 01:42:57,202
How do you think
people responded

1161
01:42:57,226 --> 01:42:59,751
to the prospect
of imminent doom?

1162
01:42:59,776 --> 01:43:03,637
They gobbled it up,
like a chocolate eclair.

1163
01:43:03,662 --> 01:43:07,346
They didn't fear their demise,
they repackaged it.

1164
01:43:07,584 --> 01:43:11,624
It can be enjoyed as video games,
as TV shows, books, movies.

1165
01:43:11,649 --> 01:43:15,113
The entire world wholeheartedly
embraced the apocalypse,

1166
01:43:15,138 --> 01:43:18,042
and sprinted towards it
with gleeful abandon.

1167
01:43:18,067 --> 01:43:21,804
Meanwhile, your earth was
crumbling all around you.

1168
01:43:21,829 --> 01:43:25,905
You got simultaneous epidemics
of obesity and starvation.

1169
01:43:25,930 --> 01:43:27,836
Explain that one.

1170
01:43:28,075 --> 01:43:30,832
Bees and butterflies
start to disappear.

1171
01:43:30,857 --> 01:43:32,597
The glaciers melt.

1172
01:43:32,622 --> 01:43:34,202
Algae blooms.

1173
01:43:34,227 --> 01:43:37,621
All around you. The coal mine
canaries are dropping dead,

1174
01:43:37,645 --> 01:43:41,119
and you won't take the hint!

1175
01:43:41,563 --> 01:43:45,041
In every moment, there is the
possibility of a better future.

1176
01:43:45,066 --> 01:43:47,009
But you people won't believe it.

1177
01:43:47,034 --> 01:43:48,265
And because you won't believe it,

1178
01:43:48,290 --> 01:43:51,303
you wouldn't do what is
necessary to make it a reality.

1179
01:43:51,335 --> 01:43:53,615
So you dwell on
this so terrible future.

1180
01:43:53,640 --> 01:43:56,569
You resign yourselves to it.
For one reason.

1181
01:43:56,594 --> 01:44:01,661
Because that future doesn't
ask anything of you today.

1182
01:44:03,208 --> 01:44:08,328
So. Yes, you saw the iceberg,
you warn the Titanic.

1183
01:44:08,893 --> 01:44:12,416
but you all just steered for
it anyway. Full steam ahead.

1184
01:44:12,441 --> 01:44:14,171
Why?

1185
01:44:14,903 --> 01:44:17,850
Because you want to sink.

1186
01:44:18,584 --> 01:44:20,821
You gave up.

1187
01:44:21,847 --> 01:44:24,103
That's not The Monitor's fault.

1188
01:44:24,128 --> 01:44:26,063
That's yours.

1189
01:44:29,790 --> 01:44:31,646
Put them through.

1190
01:44:34,700 --> 01:44:37,038
Thanks for visiting, Frank.

1191
01:44:38,164 --> 01:44:40,758
It's genuinely nice
to see you again.

1192
01:44:50,234 --> 01:44:53,088
- What are you doing?
- Not giving up.

1193
01:45:09,092 --> 01:45:10,716
Look out!

1194
01:45:15,927 --> 01:45:17,780
- Get the thing!
- What thing!

1195
01:45:17,805 --> 01:45:20,736
The thing I gave you
when we first got here.

1196
01:45:22,655 --> 01:45:24,426
Arm it!

1197
01:45:31,748 --> 01:45:34,900
Casey, the bomb!

1198
01:45:55,297 --> 01:45:56,855
- NOW WHAT !?
- Arm it!

1199
01:45:56,879 --> 01:45:58,487
HOW !?

1200
01:47:25,105 --> 01:47:26,897
Casey!

1201
01:47:30,770 --> 01:47:34,477
The bomb?
Where's the bomb?

1202
01:47:54,578 --> 01:47:57,305
<font color="#ff80ff">1 minute to detonation.</font>

1203
01:48:00,956 --> 01:48:03,447
- <font color="#ff80ff">45 seconds.</font>
- Athena!

1204
01:48:03,472 --> 01:48:05,500
Bomb. What do I do?
How do I turn it off?

1205
01:48:05,525 --> 01:48:06,934
<font color="#ff80ff">30 seconds.</font>

1206
01:48:06,959 --> 01:48:08,716
You can't.

1207
01:48:10,487 --> 01:48:11,836
Ha-ha-ha...

1208
01:48:11,861 --> 01:48:14,486
This is not 
funny.

1209
01:48:17,067 --> 01:48:20,172
Frank, get out of there!
It's gonna blow!

1210
01:48:20,953 --> 01:48:23,321
GET OUT...!

1211
01:48:25,146 --> 01:48:27,311
Get out of there!

1212
01:48:29,316 --> 01:48:31,316
- Close the portal!
- <font color="#ff80ff">1.</font>

1213
01:49:00,853 --> 01:49:03,008
- Are you alright?
- I'm fine.

1214
01:49:03,033 --> 01:49:04,346
- Can you stand?
- Yeah.

1215
01:49:04,370 --> 01:49:05,860
Frank!

1216
01:49:09,830 --> 01:49:11,094
No.

1217
01:49:31,795 --> 01:49:34,403
- What happened? Is she okay?
- I need to get her to a repair module.

1218
01:49:34,427 --> 01:49:36,000
Frank!

1219
01:49:36,046 --> 01:49:38,350
No one's going
to repair me.

1220
01:49:38,410 --> 01:49:40,372
I'm out of time.

1221
01:49:40,397 --> 01:49:43,036
I need to tell you
something now.

1222
01:49:49,982 --> 01:49:52,018
I'm done.

1223
01:49:52,239 --> 01:49:53,900
I'm shutting down.

1224
01:49:53,925 --> 01:49:55,187
I'm...

1225
01:49:55,552 --> 01:49:57,336
...shutting down.

1226
01:49:58,338 --> 01:50:00,881
I'm going to lose sync.

1227
01:50:01,553 --> 01:50:03,395
Don't look at me like that.

1228
01:50:03,420 --> 01:50:06,184
I finally think it's not...

1229
01:50:06,631 --> 01:50:08,108
failure.

1230
01:50:08,133 --> 01:50:09,854
I know.

1231
01:50:10,546 --> 01:50:14,049
There are things I need to
tell you before the final

1232
01:50:14,757 --> 01:50:17,595
Before the automative
program kicks in.

1233
01:50:18,187 --> 01:50:20,306
I'm a machine.

1234
01:50:20,331 --> 01:50:22,697
I never thought
that was bad

1235
01:50:22,722 --> 01:50:25,346
until I see your face
when you found out I was.

1236
01:50:25,371 --> 01:50:27,284
I always knew.

1237
01:50:27,779 --> 01:50:29,380
No, you didn't.

1238
01:50:29,405 --> 01:50:32,506
Systems failing.
Activating last thoughts,

1239
01:50:32,531 --> 01:50:35,483
saved for 
Frank Walker.

1240
01:50:35,640 --> 01:50:41,088
Log 15.
September 1965.

1241
01:50:41,113 --> 01:50:45,857
Frank Walker is looking at me in a
manner that is difficult to recognize.

1242
01:50:46,137 --> 01:50:49,744
It seems imperative to explain to
him that I'm an Audio Animatronic.

1243
01:50:49,769 --> 01:50:51,148
Athena.

1244
01:50:51,173 --> 01:50:54,645
But I'm concerned that he
may be adversely affected,

1245
01:50:54,670 --> 01:50:57,856
when he finds out
that I'm not human.

1246
01:50:58,132 --> 01:51:01,767
He has potential.
I don't want to damage it.

1247
01:51:02,005 --> 01:51:04,654
He needs someone
to believe in him.

1248
01:51:04,679 --> 01:51:07,319
And I'm fulfilling that need.

1249
01:51:07,344 --> 01:51:09,799
He's my top recruit.

1250
01:51:11,194 --> 01:51:16,418
Log 24.
October 1965.

1251
01:51:16,924 --> 01:51:20,125
I'm having unusual thoughts
towards Frank Walker.

1252
01:51:20,150 --> 01:51:23,398
I suspect a flaw in
my empathy interface.

1253
01:51:23,423 --> 01:51:25,730
I'm thinking I
should report it.

1254
01:51:27,464 --> 01:51:29,392
But I haven't.

1255
01:51:29,513 --> 01:51:32,022
I cannot explain why.

1256
01:51:32,584 --> 01:51:37,469
Log 78.
April 1984.

1257
01:51:37,494 --> 01:51:40,555
Frank Walker has been
banished by Governor Nix.

1258
01:51:40,580 --> 01:51:42,418
He says he's lost hope.

1259
01:51:42,443 --> 01:51:46,633
And he holds me responsible for
having given it to him in the first place.

1260
01:51:46,658 --> 01:51:48,932
I do not understand this.

1261
01:51:48,957 --> 01:51:51,226
He says I never will.

1262
01:51:51,251 --> 01:51:56,075
Because I do not feel
anger, or disappointment

1263
01:51:58,068 --> 01:51:59,661
...or love.

1264
01:52:01,661 --> 01:52:03,922
End recording.

1265
01:52:06,407 --> 01:52:09,895
I was designed to find dreamers.

1266
01:52:09,920 --> 01:52:11,947
I found you.

1267
01:52:14,388 --> 01:52:16,302
I lost you.

1268
01:52:17,916 --> 01:52:19,970
Until I found her.

1269
01:52:20,749 --> 01:52:22,404
Casey.

1270
01:52:24,902 --> 01:52:29,141
Dreamers need to
stick together.

1271
01:52:31,184 --> 01:52:33,322
It's not programming.

1272
01:52:33,797 --> 01:52:35,685
It's personal.

1273
01:52:42,819 --> 01:52:45,532
The Monitor. 
The bomb is gone.

1274
01:52:45,557 --> 01:52:48,272
But I'm not....
yet.

